{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-1709"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Manufacture of other articles of paper and paperboard"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "1709"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :paper-articles/plant-operations
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:worker-safety :environmental-stewardship :resource-efficiency]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :paper-articles-plant-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "PaperArticlesAdvisor ⊣ Paper Articles Plant Operations Governor,
 langgraph-clj StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant
 OPERATIONS COORDINATION actor for ISIC 1709's residual 'other paper
 and paperboard articles' category -- chosen concrete illustration:
 molded-pulp/paperboard paper-tableware manufacturing (paper
 plates/bowls/trays, coated and uncoated paper cups), formed on a
 pulp-molding press and finished on a die-cutting/folding line; the
 same actor shape covers this category's other n.e.c. product lines
 (filter paper, wallpaper base stock) since the coordination surface
 -- batch logging, converting-line-equipment maintenance scheduling,
 safety-concern flagging, shipment coordination -- does not vary by
 which paper article is being formed. NOT direct pulp-molding-press/
 die-cutter/converting-line-equipment control authority. Four ops
 (`:log-production-batch` / `:schedule-maintenance` /
 `:flag-safety-concern` / `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect
 :propose` only. Ten concrete governor checks elaborate this
 blueprint's HARD invariants: propose-only effect, closed op
 allowlist, closed proposal-effect allowlist (any proposal touching
 converting-line-equipment control is a hard, permanent block),
 independent equipment verification/registration before maintenance
 scheduling, independent batch verification/registration before
 shipment coordination, independent shipment-quantity recompute
 against the batch's own logged quantity, double-schedule guard,
 product-grade validation, and basis-weight/moisture-content
 plausibility validation. Safety-concern flagging (equipment hazard /
 quality defect) ALWAYS escalates to a human plant supervisor;
 `:log-production-batch` is the only op eligible to auto-commit, and
 only at phase 3 when governor-clean."}
